This document is a user manual for the WebGuard Web Browser Extension.

Firstly, how do you install the extension?
Download the source code from this github and extract it to any location you wish.
Launch a web browser, and import the extension into the browser. 

For chrome users an example of the process is as follows:
extensions > manage extensions > ensure developer mode is on > load unpacked > select the folder of the webguard extension 

there we go! Now your Webguard extension is active. You can turn the extension on and off via the extension management page of your web browser.

How do you operate the browser extension?
No user interaction is required, there are no buttons whatsoever in this extension, simply just have it running and the checks will be performed.
You will be informed if there are any vulnerabilities on the website via a popup notification box that will show up. 

When popup notification boxes show up, you may either click on "ok" or "cancel". If you choose ok, you are acknowledging the vulnerabilities but not blocking/blacklisting the website. If you choose to cancel, the website will be blocked/blacklisted for 1 minute.
Vulnerabiltiies that are detected by the extension include: SQL Injection vulnerability, XSS Vulnerabilities, CSRF Vulnerabilities, Malware Download vulnerabilities.
